location: "Cleveland, Ohio, USA"
---

Provided individualized and small-group tutoring support to undergraduate engineering students across multiple foundational courses.

Courses Tutored
======
**Mathematics**: Calculus I & II, Multivariable Calculus, Differential Equations
**Mechanics**: Statics and Strength of Materials  
**Sciences**: Chemistry for Engineers
**Electrical Engineering**: Embedded Systems Design

Tutoring Approach
======
- Conducted 7+ hours of weekly one-on-one and small-group sessions
- Developed supplementary problem sets and practice materials
- Adapted teaching methods to individual learning styles
- Monitored student progress across multiple sessions
- Connected theoretical principles to practical applications

Impact
======
Helped students strengthen understanding of core engineering concepts, develop systematic problem-solving strategies, and build confidence in challenging STEM subjects through personalized support and targeted practice.
